name: Telegram
summary: Several news outlets are reporting that Telegram's CEO, Pavel Durov, has been arrested in France. The reason for his arrest is reportedly related to Telegram's content moderation practices. The company has been criticized for not doing enough to remove extremist content from its platform. Durov's arrest has raised concerns about freedom of speech on the internet, as Telegram is a popular messaging app used by millions of people around the world. The authorities have extended Durov's detention following his arrest in Paris, and it is unclear when he will be released or what charges he may face.

name: Eagles
summary: The Philadelphia Eagles wrapped up their preseason with a 26-3 loss to the Minnesota Vikings. Despite the defeat, the Eagles inducted former running back LeSean McCoy into their Hall of Fame. Safety C.J. Gardner-Johnson expressed satisfaction with the team's depth at his position and downplayed the possibility of Jalen Mills' return. Analysts discussed the utilization of running back Saquon Barkley and the performance of the wide receivers in light of the Eagles' ongoing question marks. The Vikings praised the Eagles' strong start and defensive dominance in the game. The Eagles acquired wide receiver Jahan Dotson from the Washington Commanders in a trade, adding depth to their receiving corps. Rumors suggest the team may target a former Pro Bowl player to strengthen their roster. The Eagles signed Jason Poe while releasing C.J. Uzomah, making roster adjustments ahead of the regular season. Experts speculate on the potential impact of Jahan Dotson's addition to the Philadelphia Eagles.
